This paper deals with text style transfer, which is a natural language processing task, and specifically focuses on domain adaptation to improve performance when limited data is available. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes machine learning models to achieve domain adaptation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed models on sentiment and formality tasks, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
